<div class="row steps"> 
  <div class="col-md-1"></div>
  <div class="col-md-5 col-sm-3">
    <div class="divider-1"></div>
    <div class="block-heading-two">
      <h3><span>Why Choose Us?</span></h3>
    </div>
    <p>This web application is like none you've seen before!</p>
      <ul class="list-2">
        <li>While most personal finance applications simply track what you've spent, we help you plan for your future.</li>
        <li>Entering in your financial information is quick, easy, and painless.</li>
        <li>We can show you when all of your incomes and expenses occur in a convenient calendar view.</li>
        <li>You can finally see exactly when you can afford what without doing all of the math.</li>
      </ul>
    <br />
  </div>

  <div class="col-md-5 col-sm-3">
    <div class="divider-1"></div>
    <div class="block-heading-two">
      <h3><span>How It Works</span></h3>
    </div>
    <p>After you create an account, you can see your forecast in 4 easy steps! Click each step to learn more.</p>
      <!-- Accordion starts -->
    <div class="panel-group accordion-alt3" id="accordion-alt3">
      <!-- Panel. Use "panel-XXX" class for different colors. Replace "XXX" with color. -->
      
      <div class="panel"> 
        <!-- Panel heading -->
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-alt3" href="#collapseOne-alt3">
              <i class="fa fa-angle-right"></i> Enter your starting balance
            </a>
          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseOne-alt3" class="panel-collapse collapse">
            <!-- Panel body -->
          <div class="panel-body">
            Find out how much money you have as of today. Go to the Budget page and enter in that into the first table.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="panel">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-alt3" href="#collapseTwo-alt3">
              <i class="fa fa-angle-right"></i> Add your expected incomes and expenses
            </a>
          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseTwo-alt3" class="panel-collapse collapse">
          <div class="panel-body">
        Go to the income or expense table on the Budget page. Create a new recurring income or expense by clicking the "Add an Income" or "Add an Expense" button below the respective income and expense table. Then, fill out the short form by select the name of your income or expense, the amount, when that transaction will start, when it will end, and the frequency of the event. Click the "Add Income" or "Add Expense" button and it will be immediately entered in.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="panel">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-alt3" href="#collapseThree-alt3">
            <i class="fa fa-angle-right"></i> View your forecast
            </a>
          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseThree-alt3" class="panel-collapse collapse">
          <div class="panel-body">
        Go to the Forecast page and all of the income and expenses you entered in on the Budget page will be populated in a monthly calendar view. This app finds all the recurring dates within the start and end date based on the frequency you selected, displays them on every recurring date, and calculates the balance for every single day. 
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="panel">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-alt3" href="#collapseFour-alt3">
            <i class="fa fa-angle-right"></i> Update your information
            </a>
          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseFour-alt3" class="panel-collapse collapse">
          <div class="panel-body">
        Go to the Budget page and select the update or delete button on the right on the right of the income or expense you wish to edit. Those changes will be immediately reflected on the calendar.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>
